@startuml Device Registration Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline

title Device Registration Flow

actor "User" as User
participant "REST API" as API
participant "CommandBus" as CmdBus
participant "RegisterDeviceHandler" as Handler
participant "DeviceRegistrationService" as RegSvc
participant "DeviceRepository" as DeviceRepo
participant "DeviceConnectivityPolicy" as ConnectivityPolicy
participant "PrismaClient" as Prisma
participant "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "EventBus" as EventBus
participant "WebSocket" as WS

== Command Submission ==
User -> API: POST /api/devices\n{\n  "deviceId": "pi-001",\n  "hostname": "raspberry-pi",\n  "ipAddress": "192.168.1.100"\n}
API -> CmdBus: RegisterDeviceCommand

== Command Validation ==
CmdBus -> Handler: handle(command)
Handler -> Handler: validate(command)
Handler -> Handler: check permissions

== Domain Logic Execution ==
Handler -> RegSvc: registerDevice(params)
RegSvc -> DeviceRepo: findByIpAddress(ipAddress)
DeviceRepo -> Prisma: SELECT * FROM devices WHERE ip_address = ?
Prisma -> DB: Query execution
DB --> Prisma: Result (empty)
Prisma --> DeviceRepo: null

RegSvc -> ConnectivityPolicy: validateConnectivity(deviceData)
ConnectivityPolicy -> ConnectivityPolicy: ping device
ConnectivityPolicy -> ConnectivityPolicy: check SSH access
ConnectivityPolicy --> RegSvc: connectivity OK

RegSvc -> RegSvc: Device.create(params)
RegSvc --> Handler: Device entity

== Persistence ==
Handler -> DeviceRepo: save(device)
DeviceRepo -> Prisma: INSERT INTO devices (...)
Prisma -> DB: Execute INSERT
DB --> Prisma: Success
Prisma --> DeviceRepo: OK

== Event Publishing ==
Handler -> EventBus: publish(DeviceRegisteredEvent)
EventBus -> WS: broadcast("device:registered", event)

== Response ==
Handler --> CmdBus: success
CmdBus --> API: 201 Created\n{\n  "device": {...},\n  "message": "Device registered"\n}
API --> User: Response

== Asynchronous Processing ==
EventBus ->> EventBus: queue for async processing
note right: Background job processes:\n- Initialize monitoring\n- Send notifications\n- Update caches

@enduml
